# Required
# Add your OpenRouter API key below.
DATABASE_URL=

# Optional: separate Better Auth database URL.
# Falls back to DATABASE_URL when unset.
# AUTH_DATABASE_URL=

# Optional: enable OpenRouter models such as NVIDIA Nemotron 3 Super (free)
# Get your key at https://openrouter.ai/settings/keys
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# Optional: enable Tavily search + extract tools for OpenRouter chat models
# Get your key at https://app.tavily.com
# TAVILY_API_KEY=

# Optional: enable curated FMP MCP finance tools for OpenRouter chat models
# Uses a single server-global Financial Modeling Prep API key
# Get your key at https://financialmodelingprep.com/developer/docs/pricing
# FMP_API_KEY=

# Optional: enable OpenAI judge grading for prompt evals
# Get your key at https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Optional judge model override for prompt evals
# OPENAI_EVAL_JUDGE_MODEL=gpt-5.4

BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=
BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
# Optional shared parent cookie domain for cross-subdomain Better Auth sessions.
# Example: BETTER_AUTH_COOKIE_DOMAIN=chloei.ai
# BETTER_AUTH_COOKIE_DOMAIN=
# Optional comma-separated list of additional trusted origins for Better Auth.
# Example: BETTER_AUTH_TRUSTED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000
# BETTER_AUTH_TRUSTED_ORIGINS=
# On Vercel:
# - Set BETTER_AUTH_URL only for production, for example https://chloei.ai
# - Omit BETTER_AUTH_URL in preview so Better Auth can use VERCEL_URL automatically
# - Set BETTER_AUTH_TRUSTED_ORIGINS to any additional custom origins such as https://www.chloei.ai
# - Set BETTER_AUTH_COOKIE_DOMAIN only in production when you need shared cookies on a parent domain

# Optional agent request limit overrides.
# Safe defaults are enabled in code even when these remain commented out.
# AGENT_MAX_MESSAGES=50
# AGENT_MAX_MESSAGE_CHARS=12000
# AGENT_MAX_TOTAL_CHARS=48000
# AGENT_TOOL_MAX_STEPS=12

# Optional streaming timeout override in milliseconds
# AGENT_STREAM_TIMEOUT_MS=300000

# Optional absolute prompt-context directory for SOUL.md and related agent files
# Defaults to ./agent-context when unset
# AGENT_CONTEXT_DIR=/absolute/path/to/agent-context

# Optional in-memory rate limit overrides.
# Rate limiting is enabled by default unless you explicitly disable it.
# AGENT_RATE_LIMIT_ENABLED=true
# AGENT_RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=60000
# AGENT_RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=60
# AGENT_MAX_CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_CLIENT=4

# Optional Next.js request body limits
# NEXT_SERVER_ACTIONS_BODY_SIZE_LIMIT=1mb
# NEXT_PROXY_CLIENT_MAX_BODY_SIZE=1mb

# Notes
# - Leave optional values commented out to use the safe defaults from code.
# - Thread storage now requires `pnpm migrate` before serving traffic.
# - Runtime config lives in `src/lib/server/agent-runtime-config.ts`.
# - FMP MCP integration lives in `src/lib/server/llm/ai-sdk-fmp-mcp-tools.ts`.
# - Prompt-context composition lives in `src/lib/server/agent-context.ts`.
# - Shared prompt-context files live in `agent-context/`.
# - Per-user overrides live in `agent-context/users/<encodeURIComponent(userId)>/USER.md` and `MEMORY.md`.
# - `HEARTBEAT.md` is scaffold-only in Agent Context Files v1 and is not executed.
# - `vercel env pull .env.local` is the quickest way to hydrate local development from Vercel.
# - Next.js body-size parsing lives in `next.config.mjs`.
# - Better Auth uses `BETTER_AUTH_URL` as the canonical app origin when set and otherwise falls back to Vercel system URLs.
# - `BETTER_AUTH_TRUSTED_ORIGINS` lets you allow additional origins such as `www`.
# - `AUTH_DATABASE_URL` lets you share Better Auth users/sessions across apps without moving app data.
# - `BETTER_AUTH_COOKIE_DOMAIN` enables shared auth cookies across trusted subdomains.
